The University of Fort Hare has announced that there are 125 confirmed Covid-19 cases at the university. According to spokesperson Tandi Mapukata, the East London campus has 27 new cases - including 25 students, a driver and a security guard. The university now has 60 active cases, 61 recoveries, four fatalities with a total of 125 confirmed cases. "The majority of the infected students are in the faculty of law, followed by management and commerce and a couple from health sciences," Mapukata said on Wednesday. Two of the students have recovered and will be released from isolation. DispatchLIVE